    "#creates a defined function to clean the text of punct and blanks\n",
    "def clean_txt(text):\n",
    "    text=text.lower()\n",
    "    text=re.sub('[^a-zA_Z0-9]',\" \",text)\n",
    "    text=re.sub('\\\\d|\\\\W+|_',' ',text)\n",
    "    return text"
   ]
  },

    "# creates a defined function to tokenize the text and remove stop words\n",
    "def token_no_stop(text):\n",
    "    stop_wordz = stopwords.words('english')\n",
    "    tokens = word_tokenize(text)\n",
    "    txt_nostop = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_wordz]\n",
    "    return txt_nostop"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['review_no_stop'] = df['review_cleaned'].apply(token_no_stop) \n",

    "# Use the sklearn function to easily split the data into test and train. \n",

   "source": [
    "# Here on the test data, we DON'T REFIT the transform, we just apply transform to see how it did later on\n",
